# Cross-platform line endings for the dotclaude config repo.
# Repo stores LF; the working tree gets the right EOL per file type so scripts
# run correctly whether checked out on Windows, macOS, or Linux.

# Default: normalize to LF in the repo and the working tree (stops Windows
# CRLF churn and keeps diffs clean).
*           text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts MUST be LF — they are executed by bash on macOS/Linux.
*.sh        text eol=lf

# PowerShell scripts: CRLF in the working tree (Windows convention).
*.ps1       text eol=crlf

# Markdown / Python / config are fine as LF everywhere (inherit the default).

# Binary assets — never munge line endings.
*.png       binary
*.jpg       binary
*.jpeg      binary
*.gif       binary
*.ico       binary
*.pdf       binary
